            "weighting": "<dd>45%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p>Planning document submission in Week 7. 11/09/2026</p>\n<p>Presentation slides and research portfolio submission in Week 12. Team presentations will be completed during tutorials in Weeks 12 and 13. 19/10/2026</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L02, L03, L04, L05",
            "mode": "Oral, Product/ Artefact/ Multimedia, Written",
            "category": "Paper/ Report/ Annotation, Presentation",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>For this assessment, students will identify a marketing problem and develop a problem-based consumer behaviour case study. The case study should explain how consumers’ perceptions, attitudes, motivations, cultures or behaviours influence purchasing, social actions and decision-making.</p>\n<p>Students must collect primary research by conducting THREE consumer interviews, supported by secondary research drawn from academic journals, industry reports and marketing literature.</p>\n<p>The assessment has two components:</p>\n<p><strong>PART A: Planning Document (10%) – Submission due Week 7</strong></p>\n<p>The planning document outlines how information and data will be collected for the written case study.</p>\n<p><strong>PART B: Case Study Presentation (35%) – Submission due Week 12</strong></p>\n<p>Teams will present their case study findings during tutorials in Weeks 12 and 13. All team members must present for the presentations. Presentations are 20 minutes (15 minutes presenting and 5 minutes for Q&amp;A).</p>\n<p>Required submissions include:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Presentation slides (20%)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Research portfolio (5%)</strong>, which acts as a supporting document demonstrating the team’s research process and evidence base</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There will be a <strong>10% individual mark</strong>, influenced by presentation performance and demonstrated contribution to teamwork. This includes evidence from the team contract (Week 4) and peer evaluations, which will inform adjustments where necessary.</p>\n<p><strong>Teamwork</strong></p>\n<p>Teams will be formed in Week 2 and finalised in Week 3, with the team list and topic submitted to the tutor. Teams must be formed within the same tutorial group and may include up to FIVE students.</p>\n<p>Students who enrol late or do not engage early may be required to complete the assessment individually or in a smaller team. Teams are expected to monitor contributions throughout the semester and raise issues with the tutor promptly. Where individuals do not contribute, marks may be deducted to reflect their participation, including the possibility of receiving zero. Students should keep records of their work to verify contributions.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Follow assessment links from blackboard.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>A <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">penalty</a> of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
